Bio
Roy Beveridge, MD, is a member of the Health Care Payment Learning & Action Network’s Guiding Committee. He serves as Senior Vice President and Chief Medical Officer (CMO) for Humana where he is responsible for developing and implementing Humana’s clinical strategy with an emphasis on advancing the company’s integrated care delivery model, especially in the areas of quality and cost improvement. Previously, Dr. Beveridge served as CMO for McKesson Specialty Health. Prior to McKesson’s acquisition of US Oncology in 2010, Dr. Beveridge served as Executive Vice President and Medical Director at US Oncology. Dr. Beveridge also was Co-director of the Bone Marrow Transplant Program at Inova Fairfax Hospital in Falls Church, Virginia. Board certified in medical oncology and internal medicine, Dr. Beveridge has authored numerous articles on a wide range of medical topics such as hematology, stem cell transplantation, and quality and value-based medical practice. Dr. Beveridge earned a bachelor of arts degree from Johns Hopkins University and a medical degree from Cornell University Medical College. He completed his residency in internal medicine at University of Chicago Hospital and his fellowship at Johns Hopkins Hospital.

















