Humana Chief Medical Officer Roy Beveridge, M.D., welcomes you





We’re excited to have you come and learn more about the work we’re doing to improve people’s health by making the health care system less fragmented and more integrated. Humana is a rapidly changing company that is a leader in both population health and in the conversion from a “traditional” insurer to a true “integrated health delivery company.” 
We’re hoping you’ll join us as a member of our innovative program designed to bring physician leaders to Humana. Our rotational program will utilize the leadership skills you’ve already developed, immersing you in key areas within our company with intense executive mentorship and structured learning. Our goal is to foster the development of the next generation of physician leaders within Humana.
Learn more about our CMO

Dr. Beveridge Bio


















About the office of the CMO


One of the main focus areas of the office of the chief medical officer is to help physicians improve the health of their patients. Working alongside clinicians, we look for new ways to elevate the quality of care and health outcomes of each individual patient. Learn more about how the office of the CMO is helping to improve population health. 









Browse our publications


The office of the chief medical officer continually advocates for improvements to the health system. One way we do that is by partnering with academic centers and professional organizations to conduct research that is peer-reviewed, reliable and relevant.
Our research publications can be found at humana.com/research 
The following two studies are examples of these valuable partnerships:
Synchronization of Medication Refill Dates and Adherence
In this prospective-controlled study, synchronizing prescription refill dates of multiple medications increased adherence by up to 4 percentage points relative to control.  
Leveraging Health-related Quality of Life in Population Health Management: The Case for Healthy Days
In this article, the authors describe the CDC’s quality of life tool, Healthy Days, and why quality of life is so important in improving health.









We work hard to create awareness


In addition to ongoing research, the office of the chief medical officer also maintains a presence in popular medical publications through guest columns or informative articles. 

















Simplicity in health care


Together with Centers for Medicaid & Medicare Services (CMS) and other commercial payers, we’re working toward consistency in reporting for physicians. 



 
Read the article (opens in new window) 



















Healthy Days


Dr. Beveridge talks about measuring population health improvement through the use of the Healthy Days measure.



 
